The paper focuses on testing graphical user interfaces (GUIs) and proposes a new model, called an event-dependency graph (EDG), to capture data dependencies between the code of event handlers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing bytecode and automating the construction of the EDG, which could fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Development (cs.SD) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of GUI testing, which could relate to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a "grey-box" approach, which involves both black-box and white-box testing techniques, and could potentially fall under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
